    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "Zayd b. Ali b. al-Husayn (as), the son of the fourth Imam and brother of the fifth Imam, testified that in every era, Allah appoints a man from the Ahl al-Bayt as a proof (hujja) over His creation. He identified the proof of his own time as his nephew, Imam Ja'far b. Muhammad (al-Sadiq), declaring that whoever follows him is rightly guided and whoever opposes him remains unguided. This testimony is significant because it comes from a member of the Ahl al-Bayt who himself was revered, yet he pointed to Imam al-Sadiq as the divinely appointed authority.",
        "key_terms": {
          "يحتج": "Uses as a proof/argument (ihtijaj); Allah establishes a hujja (proof) among humanity",
          "حجة": "Proof (hujja); the divinely appointed authority who serves as evidence of God's guidance on earth",
          "أهل البيت": "The People of the House; the Prophet's household, specifically the Imams"
        },
        "seo_question": "What did Zayd b. Ali say about the Proof (Hujja) of every age?"
      },
      "ur": {
        "summary": "زید بن علی بن الحسین (ع) نے فرمایا کہ ہر زمانے میں ہم اہل بیت میں سے ایک شخص ہوتا ہے جسے اللہ اپنی مخلوق پر حجت قرار دیتا ہے۔ آپ نے اپنے زمانے کی حجت اپنے بھتیجے امام جعفر بن محمد (الصادق) کو قرار دیا۔",
        "key_terms": {
          "يحتج": "حجت قائم کرنا؛ اللہ کا بندوں پر دلیل قائم کرنا",
          "حجة": "حجت؛ خدا کی طرف سے مقرر کردہ اختیار",
